#Text=Seward
#Text=Seward ( " SOO-word " ) is a small port city ( population ~2,700 ) located at the head of Resurrection Bay on the Kenai Peninsula in Southcentral Alaska .
#Text=Seward was named in honor of William H. Seward , President Abraham Lincoln 's Secretary of State , who was responsible for negotiating the purchase of Alaska from Russia in 1867 .
#Text=Understand

#Text=Founded in 1903 as the ocean terminus of what is now the Alaska Railroad , Seward prides itself , not only on its natural beauty , but as Alaska 's only deep-water , ice-free port with rail , highway and air transportation to Alaska 's interior and major urban population centers .
#Text=For local events and news see SewardCityNews.com , Seward 's citizen journalism website .
#Text=By car
#Text=Seward is located 127 road miles south of Anchorage .
#Text=The Seward Highway is a very scenic 2.5-hour drive from Anchorage to Seward , but can be slow in peak summer .

#Text=In 2017 the Alaska Department of Transportation announced a 4-year 2-phase Milepost 75-90 Rehabilitation Project to make major safety improvements to a busy crash-prone section of the Seward Highway from Girdwood to beyond the Portage curve toward Turnagain Pass .

#Text=In July 2015 a tour bus crash at Milepost 79 ( Portage Glacier Road and Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center ) killed one man and critically injured several others , causing a 10-hour traffic jam .
#Text=During the summer months , up to 15,000 vehicles use this 15-mile stretch of Seward Highway daily .
#Text=Although the project is not yet fully funded , construction on Seward Highway is scheduled to begin 2018 .
#Text=By train
#Text=The Alaska Railroad offers daily rail passage between Anchorage and Seward in the summer , May 13 to Sept 14 .
#Text=The trip between Anchorage and Seward -- the Coastal Classic -- is arguably its most scenic section , and you can take the train one-way .
#Text=The train parallels the Seward Highway along the Turnagain Arm , but also heads up into the mountains away from the road , pass glaciers and alpine meadows you wo n't be able to see by car .

#Text=Adventure Class ( with shared access to older vista dome railcar ) Round Trip/One Way fare : $119/$ 75 adults , $59/$ 38 children ( 2-11 ) ; GoldStar Service ( New Dome Railcar ) Round Trip/One Way fare : $219/$ 130 adults , $110/$ 65 children .

#Text=Passengers are required by TSA to check-in at the ticket window ( hour before at Anchorage , 30-45 minutes before at Seward ) and show a government issued photo ID ( for those age 18 and older ) to receive boarding passes .
#Text=If you have luggage ( 2 pieces max ) , it must be checked through to your destination .
#Text=At depots , boarding for trains occurs 20-30 minutes prior to the scheduled departure .
#Text=Southbound
#Text=6:45AM - Depart Anchorage Depot - 411 West 1st Avenue
#Text=11:05AM - Arrive Seward Depot - 410 Port Avenue ( short walk to small boat harbor ; about 1/2 mile to cruise ship dock )
#Text=Northbound
#Text=6PM - Depart Seward Depot
#Text=10:15PM - Arrive Anchorage Depot
#Text=By bus
#Text=The Park Connection , 1-800-208-0200 , offers twice daily bus service between Anchorage and Seward in the summer , mid-May to mid-September .
#Text=Check in 15 minutes prior ; luggage 2 pieces max .
#Text=In general , the trip by bus is faster than by train , but slower than by car .
#Text=Southbound AM
#Text=7AM - Depart Anchorage - Egan Center : $ 55
#Text=9:45AM - Arrive Seward Small Boat Harbor

#Text=By ship
#Text=The Dale R. Lindsey Alaska Railroad Seward Intermodal Terminal ( " cruise-ship dock " to locals ) , 913 Port Ave , is where cruise ships moor .
#Text=Ships tie up directly to the dock , and no tenders are used to transport guests between the ship and shore .
#Text=The Alaska Railroad uses this facility for freight .
#Text=From May to September , about 50 ships arrive and depart Seward 's port as part of the popular 7-14 day Alaska cruises , round-the-world itineraries , and special charter cruises .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Seward is a great place to walk around .
#Text=For those needing a ride , here are some options .
#Text=Summer Shuttle Bus , +1 907-224-4020 , is operated daily by the city of Seward during the summer months when the cruise ships are in town .
#Text=The shuttle makes a half hour loop starting at the cruise ship dock to the Alaska SeaLife Center and back . $ 5 pp , good for entire day .
#Text=Tidewater Taxi +1 907-727-1929 .
#Text=Water taxi servicing Resurrection Bay , Kayakers Cove , Alaska State Park Cabins and elsewhere .
#Text=Hertz of Seward , 907-224-4378 .
#Text=Rentals for a day or longer with one-way drop off in Anchorage available .
#Text=Seward Bike Shop , 411 Port Ave. , 907-224-2448 , sewardbikeshop.com .
#Text=Rents bikes by the hour or day .
#Text=There is a bike path along the water from the harbor to the front of town .
#Text=PJ'S Taxis , 907-224-5555 .
#Text=See
#Text=The Sealife Center , 301 Railway Ave , ☏ +1907 224-6300 , toll-free : +1-800 224-2525 .
#Text=Aquarium and research facility featuring marine life of the Gulf of Alaska .
#Text=The Sealife Center is Alaska ’s only public aquarium and ocean wildlife rescue center .
#Text=Exhibits feature puffins , octopus , sea lions and other sealife . $ 20 adult , $ 15 student ( 12-17 ) , $ 10 child ( 4-11 ) , age 3 and under free .
#Text=Exit Glacier .
#Text=Exit Glacier is the only part of Kenai Fjords National Park accessible by road .
#Text=Here you can stroll the trails , walk very close to an active glacier or take a ranger-led walk .
#Text=It is a place where you can witness up close how glaciers re-shape a landscape and learn how plant life reclaims the barren rocky land exposed by a glacier 's retreat .
#Text=Do

#Text=Sewards highlights are the neighboring Kenai Fjords National Park , sport fishing ( for salmon , halibut , ling cod and salmon shark ) , glacier and wildlife day cruises , kayaking , sailing , hiking and mountain biking , quaint and quirky townsfolk , 4th of July celebrations and the Silver Salmon Derby .
#Text=Stoney Creek Canopy Adventures .
#Text=- located in Seward
#Text=4th of July Mount Marathon Race .
#Text=Three miles up and down , complete with cliffs , waterfalls , and loose sharp rocks , a great Alaskan event
#Text=Seavey 's Ididaride , Exit Glacier Rd .
#Text=Here you can see one of the family 's 3 dog yards .
#Text=Go for a ride on a buggy with a team of dogs , play with puppies , and get up close and personal with Mitch 's gear and sled .
#Text=You get a tour guide through the property and learn about the grueling ididarod race .
